The Federal Government will Wednesday fulfill it’s long time promise to the former Super Eagles Coach, Bonfrere Jo for winning the FIFA World Cup 1994 for Nigeria. The previous administrations as at the period promised a befitting housing apartment for the ex-Super Eagles Coach but it remained unfulfilled until 24 years after. According to the Director of Information, Federal Ministry of Power Works and Housing, Theodore Ogaziechi, the house which is located in Kuje, Federal Capital Territory is completed and already painted. The Minister of Power Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola is to personally hand over the keys to the Coach today in Abuja. Details later…